LAGOS, April 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian police said on Saturday they were on the trail of some gunmen who abducted two people in the country's central region. The wife and daughter of a state official in the Plateau state were abducted in the early hours of Saturday from their residence in the Mangu local government area of the state, said Ubah Ogaba, the spokesman for the police in Plateau. He said in a brief statement that police operatives were already on the trail of the abductors on the way to rescue the two people. A series of gunmen attacks recently happened in the most populous African country, resulting in civilian deaths and the kidnapping of people.  â– 